### 2. Reduce `continue` usage in the loop

Sonar is complaining because you have multiple `continue`s.
Refactor the loop into a single gate.

### Current style

```java
for (String failedKey : failedFiles) {
    String fileName = Paths.get(failedKey).getFileName().toString();

    if (!isValidRetryFile(fileName)) {
        continue;
    }

    String retryKey = failedKey.replaceFirst(FAILED_PREFIX, RETRYING_PREFIX);
    boolean claimed = cosStorageService.moveIfExists(failedKey, retryKey);

    if (!claimed) {
        continue;
    }

    ...
}
```

### Better style

```java
for (String failedKey : failedFiles) {
    String fileName = Paths.get(failedKey).getFileName().toString();

    if (isValidRetryFile(fileName)) {
        processRetryFile(failedFiles, failedKey, fileName);
    }
}
```

Then move the rest into a helper:

```java
private void processRetryFile(List<String> failedFiles, String failedKey, String fileName) {
    String retryKey = failedKey.replaceFirst(FAILED_PREFIX, RETRYING_PREFIX);
    boolean claimed = cosStorageService.moveIfExists(failedKey, retryKey);

    if (claimed) {
        try {
            log.info("Retrying transfer for {}", fileName);
            cftApiClient.notifyAndWaitForCompletion(retryKey, fileName, RETRY_WAIT);
            cleanupFilesWithSameBase(failedFiles, fileName);
            cosStorageService.deleteFile(retryKey);
            log.info("Retry successful for {}", fileName);
        } catch (Exception ex) {
            log.warn("Retry failed for {}", retryKey, ex);
            String failedAgain = retryKey.replaceFirst(RETRYING_PREFIX, FAILED_PREFIX);
            cosStorageService.moveFile(retryKey, failedAgain);
        }
    }
}
```

That usually satisfies Sonar and also makes the code cleaner.

