# 2. `InvoiceJobScheduler` coverage

Very easy to cover.

You likely have two methods:

* one launching main job
* one launching retry job

Create a unit test mocking `JobLauncher`, `Job`, maybe `JobExplorer` if used.

Example:

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class InvoiceJobSchedulerTest {

    @Mock
    private JobLauncher jobLauncher;

    @Mock
    private Job invoiceJob;

    @Mock
    private Job retryFailedTransfersJob;

    @InjectMocks
    private InvoiceJobScheduler scheduler;

    @Test
    void shouldLaunchInvoiceJob() throws Exception {
        scheduler.runInvoiceJob();
        verify(jobLauncher).run(eq(invoiceJob), any());
    }

    @Test
    void shouldLaunchRetryJob() throws Exception {
        scheduler.runRetryJob();
        verify(jobLauncher).run(eq(retryFailedTransfersJob), any());
    }
}
```

